title: A kind of Starch Based Biodegradable Plastics applied to packaging for foodstuff
assignees: Sichuan Xinda Enterprise Group Co Ltd

events.title: Application filed by Sichuan Xinda Enterprise Group Co Ltd
events.assignee_search: Sichuan Xinda Enterprise Group Co Ltd

classifications.description: Starch; Degradation products thereof, e.g. dextrin
Polymer mixtures characterised by other features containing three or more polymers in a blend containing four or more polymers in a blend

abstract: The present invention relates to degradation material preparing technical field, especially a kind of Starch Based Biodegradable Plastics applied to packaging for foodstuff；The mass fraction composition of the Starch Based Biodegradable Plastics applied to packaging for foodstuff is as follows：50 60 parts of starch, 18 26 parts of polypropylene, 6 12 parts of poly butylene succinate, 2 12 parts of glass fibre, 1.2 2.0 parts of calcium stearate, 2.4 4.8 parts of string, 1.2 3.6 parts of dispersant, 6 14 parts of plasticizer, 0.6 2.6 parts of coupling agent.In degradation plastic, this natural high molecular substance of starch have the advantages that wide material sources, cheap, the regeneration period is short, can it is degradable in a variety of contexts, any pollution will not be produced to environment, be the good Natural Degradation material of development prospect.Starch that the present invention uses, string, poly butylene succinate are degradation material, significantly improve the degradation property of material, and are acted synergistically by coupling agent and dispersant, control starch cohesion and string between reunion.
claims:
1. a kind of Starch Based Biodegradable Plastics applied to packaging for foodstuff, it is characterised in that the starch-based bio is degradable
Plastics：Using starch filled polypropylene, Starch Based Biodegradable Plastics master batch is made by extrusion by melting, its raw material components
By weight, it is formulated as follows：Starch 50-60 parts, polypropylene 18-26 parts, poly butylene succinate 6-12 parts, glass fibre 2-
12 parts, calcium stearate 1.2-2.0 parts, string 2.4-4.8 parts, dispersant 1.2-3.6 parts, plasticizer 6-14 parts, coupling agent
0.6-2.6 parts.

2. it is applied to the Starch Based Biodegradable Plastics of packaging for foodstuff as claimed in claim 1, it is characterised in that described
Starch is one kind in tapioca, farina or cornstarch.

3. it is applied to the Starch Based Biodegradable Plastics of packaging for foodstuff as claimed in claim 1, it is characterised in that described
String is bamboo fibre, one or more of compoundings in stalk fibre, rice hull cellulose, flax fiber.

4. it is applied to the Starch Based Biodegradable Plastics of packaging for foodstuff as claimed in claim 1, it is characterised in that described
The length of string is 5.0-8.0 μm.

5. it is applied to the Starch Based Biodegradable Plastics of packaging for foodstuff as claimed in claim 1, it is characterised in that described
Dispersant is；One kind in vinyl bis-stearamides, glyceryl monostearate, glyceryl tristearate.

6. it is applied to the Starch Based Biodegradable Plastics of packaging for foodstuff as claimed in claim 1, it is characterised in that described
Plasticizer is ATBC, tributyl 2-acetylcitrate, one kind of diethylene glycol dibenzoate.

7. it is applied to the Starch Based Biodegradable Plastics of packaging for foodstuff as claimed in claim 1, it is characterised in that described
Silane coupler is one kind in KH-550, YDH-151 or KH-570.

8. it is applied to the Starch Based Biodegradable Plastics of packaging for foodstuff as claimed in claim 1, it is characterised in that：Pass through
Coupling agent and dispersant act synergistically, in the compatibility of lifting starch, string and polypropylene, poly butylene succinate
Meanwhile control starch material cohesion and string between reunion.

9. it is applied to the preparation side of the Starch Based Biodegradable Plastics of packaging for foodstuff described in a kind of any one of claim 1-8
Method, it is characterised in that comprise the following steps：
      (1) 18-26 parts polypropylene, 6-12 parts poly butylene succinate, 2.4-4.8 part strings are weighed, adds high mixer,
The mixed 1-3min of height；
      (2) pretreatment of starch, 80 degrees Celsius of 4 hours of drying；50-60 part starch is weighed, adds step（1）Described height mixes
In machine, the mixed 2-4min of height；Continuously add calcium stearate 1.2-2.0 parts, dispersant 1.2-3.6 parts, plasticizer 6-14 parts, coupling agent
0.6-2.6 parts, the mixed 2-4min of height, take out standby；
      (3) by step（2）Resulting material adds double screw extruder, in 170-190 DEG C of temperature, rotating speed 260-300, main feeding
Frequency 7-9, side feeding frequency 0 process conditions under be granulated, in extrusion add 2-12 part glass fibres, prepare institute of the present invention
The Starch Based Biodegradable Plastics applied to packaging for foodstuff stated.
